description:
MQ - Mini Quantum 8 Bit

This computer is based off of Quantum Computer v2300, which is my previous working computer. This is my attempts at making it better.

Out of box specs:
Cache size: 16 bytes (max: 256)
Stack size: 16 bytes (max: 256)
Program memory size: 64 words (max: 256)
AVG Speed: 20 ticks (500 ms)
Port ax: 256)

Operation codes:
0 - NOP - No operation
1 - LRA - Load Register ACC
2 - SRA - Store Register ACC
3 - CALL - Call
4 - RET - Return
5 - JMP - Jump
6 - JMPP - Jump Positive
7 - JMPZ - Jump Zero
8 - JMPN - Jump Negative
9 - JMPC - Jump Carry
10 - CCF - Clear Register Carry
...
16 - AND - bitwise AND
17 - OR - bitwise OR
18 - XOR - bitwise XOR
19 - NOT - bitwise NOT
20 - LSC - Left Shift Carry
21 - RSC - Right Shift Carry
22 - CMP - Compare
...
48 - UI - User Input
49 - UO - User Output
...
32 - ADC - Add Carry
33 - SBC - Subtract Carry
34 - INC - Increment
35 - DEC - Decrement
36 - ABS - Absolute
...
112 - PRW - Port Register Write
113 - PRR - Port Register Read
...
127 - HALT - Halt
name: MQ VANILA Computer
